<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1>Embedding AI Literacy within the Communication Basic Course</h1>
        <img src="penn_state_logo.png" alt="Penn State Logo" class="penn-state-logo">
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <section class="section">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Penn State University is at the forefront of educational innovation, recognizing the critical importance of AI literacy in today's digital landscape. We are excited to announce our project, "Embedding AI Literacy within the Communication Basic Course," aimed at integrating essential AI literacy objectives into CAS 100 Effective Speech.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Project Overview</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Goal:</strong> To equip all Penn State students with the ability to understand, use, monitor, and critically reflect on AI applications, particularly generative AI (GAI) tools, through the foundational communication course, CAS 100.</li>
                <li><strong>Rationale:</strong> As GAI becomes integral to media and rhetoric, it's crucial to extend media literacy efforts into GAI literacy within the communication basic course, a general education requirement for all Penn State students.</li>
                <li><strong>Outcomes:</strong> Development of accessible and adaptable modules within Canvas and a Pressbook OER, enabling instructors to easily incorporate AI literacy objectives into their CAS 100 courses.</li>
                <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Utilizing the AI literacy framework by Ng et al. (2021), the modules will cover:
                    <ul>
                        <li><img src="understanding_icon.png" alt="Understanding" class="icon"> Understanding basic AI concepts.</li>
                        <li><img src="applying_icon.png" alt="Applying" class="icon"> Applying AI knowledge.</li>
                        <li><img src="evaluation_icon.png" alt="Evaluating" class="icon"> Evaluating and creating with GAI tools.</li>
                        <li><img src="ethics_icon.png" alt="Ethics" class="icon"> Addressing ethical concerns related to GAI.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Alignment:</strong> This initiative aligns with Penn State's strategic goals of "transforming education" and "empowering through digital education," as well as the CAS 100 learning objectives of Effective Communication and Critical and Analytic Thinking.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Project Timeline (Key Milestones)</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Fall 2024:</strong> Project setup, research, student worker hire, initial assessments.</li>
                <li><strong>Spring 2025:</strong> IRB submission, Canvas module development, faculty recruitment, symposium presentation, OER Pressbook Development.</li>
                <li><strong>Summer 2025:</strong> Pre-test survey, module finalization, technology re-evaluation.</li>
                <li><strong>Fall 2025:</strong> Module implementation, pre/post-testing.</li>
                <li><strong>Spring 2026:</strong> Evaluation, faculty feedback, symposium presentation, project roll-off planning.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="call-to-action">
            <h2>Call to Action: Join Our Initiative!</h2>
            <p>We are seeking passionate individuals to contribute to the success of this project:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Chapter Contributions:</strong> We invite educators and researchers to contribute chapters to our Open Educational Resource (OER) Pressbook. Share your expertise and insights on AI literacy in communication.</li>
                <li><strong>Peer Reviewers:</strong> Help us ensure the quality and accuracy of our materials by serving as a peer reviewer for our OER Pressbook and Canvas modules.</li>
                <li><strong>Pilot Testers:</strong> Be among the first to implement our AI literacy modules in your CAS 100 courses. Your feedback is invaluable in refining our resources.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
